title: FileKeyValueStoreTest fails in a clean project
body:
### Description

The first time I build the project, the `FileKeyValueStoreTest.testConcurent` fails with a `TimeoutException`. If build again, the test will pass. All subsequent builds without a clean will also pass. If I do a clean then a build, the build will fail.

### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)

1. Run `./gradlew clean build`

**Expected behavior:**

I expect this test to pass when built in a clean project.

**Actual behavior:**

This test fails.

**Frequency:**

It happens every time for me.

### Versions
* Software version: master (e61f57d01d49e6937b1b05adca9a625a05b60a95)
* Java version: openjdk version "11.0.16.1" 2022-08-12
* OS Name & Version: macOS

I think this was because `DatabaseTest` was using a huge amount of disk IOPs so `FileKeyValueStoreTest` wound up taking longer than expected (on a second build the result of `DatabaseTest` is cached avoiding the issue).  We've moved `DatabaseTest` to integration tests which is more reflective of the type of test it is and I haven't seen this issue again since. Closing for now, but reopen if you're still seeing it.
